Package: typely
Version: 1.0.1
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.11), python3-venv, python3-dev, portaudio19-dev, libportaudio2, ffmpeg, xclip, xdotool, libportaudio2
Recommends: python3-pip
Maintainer: Typely Developers <dev@typely.app>
Description: Speech-to-text transcription tray application
 Typely is an Ubuntu Linux tray application for speech-to-text
 transcription using local Whisper models or Groq API.
 Features:
  - Tray-first workflow
  - Global hotkeys for toggle and hold-to-talk recording
  - Local Whisper transcription via faster-whisper
  - Optional Groq transcription provider
  - Silence auto-stop with configurable timeout
